⚫As the #BlackHole at the center of galaxy Markarian 573 pulls matter towards itself, matter in the disk outside of the black hole is heated up by extreme forces and produces light. A surrounding ring of dust & gas obscures some of this light, giving this galaxy an hourglass shape.⏳

